<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
    <title>WebTrack • Educational Demo</title>

    <style>
        .warning-box {
          border: 2px solid #dc3545;
          background-color: #f8d7da;
          color: #721c24;
          padding: 1rem;
          margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
          border-radius: 0.375rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <main class="container">
        <section class="hero-section text-center">
            <div class="container">
                <h1 class="display-4">WebTrack</h1>
                <p class="lead">
                    Real‑time user activity monitoring educational demo.
                </p>

                <div class="warning-box">
                    <strong>Warning:</strong> This project is provided for educational purposes only.
                    Understanding how user activity can be monitored is important — but unauthorized
                    tracking of individuals may be illegal and unethical.
                </div>

                <a href="https://github.com/GeorgiMY/WebTrack" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" target="_blank">
                    View on GitHub
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="my-5">
            <h2>About WebTrack</h2>
            <p>
                <strong>WebTrack</strong> is a web application that allows you to observe what each
                user is doing on a website in real time. Its purpose is to demonstrate how trivial
                it can be for a server to monitor user behaviour online — often without a visitor
                being aware that such monitoring is occurring. :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}
            </p>

            <div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert">
                ⚠️ <strong>Important Advisory:</strong> This tool is intended for demonstration,
                testing, or research. It is not a finished security product and should not be
                deployed against live systems without explicit permission. Misuse may violate
                privacy laws or user consent requirements.
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="my-5">
            <h2>Features</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Real‑time event tracking</li>
                <li>Control panel to view active sessions</li>
                <li>Educational insights into web monitoring</li>
                <li>ASP.NET backend with SignalR and Vue front‑end</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="my-5">
            <h2>Technologies</h2>
            <p>Main languages and components used in the project include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>C# and ASP.NET for backend logic</li>
                <li>Vue.js for front‑end UI</li>
                <li>SignalR for real‑time communication</li>
                <li>TailwindCSS (used within UI) :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>
</body>
</html>